FBIS4-36337 "drnes110_s_94005" FBIS-NES-94-110 Daily Report 7 Jun 1994 Iran Foreign Ministry Affirms Neutral Position on Yemen Foreign Ministry Affirms Neutral Position on Yemen LD0706115694 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 7 Jun 94 LD0706115694 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Text] A spokesman for our country's Foreign Ministry rejected the claim that Tehran supports one side of the conflict in Yemen and is dispatching military assistance to that country. He stated: From the start of the conflict the Islamic Republic of Iran clearly expressed its regret over the outbreak of the war and expressed its concern about the possible separation of the Muslim brothers in Yemen. He added: By adopting a neutral stance Iran has announced its readiness to mediate. The Foreign Ministry spokesman stressed: Iran is in favor of Yemen's unity and resolving the existing disputes through peaceful means, bearing in mind the national interests of the people of Yemen.
